Aaron Burr ran for Governor,

137
00:08:45,980 --> 00:08:47,030
卡尔霍恩也曾竞选过参议员
Calhoun for the Senate.

138
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,180
那都是两百年前的事了
200 years ago.

139
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:50,810
一个曾在决斗中杀人  另一个支持奴隶制
One shot a man in a duel, the other believed in slavery.

140
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:50,810
阿伦・伯尔在决斗中杀死了亚历山大・哈密尔顿
卡尔霍恩主张奴隶制度是完美的制度

141
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:53,090
我们真要跟这种人相比吗  弗兰克
Is that really the sort of company we wanna share, Frank?

142
00:08:53,090 --> 00:08:54,740
总统先生  我们可能要
Mr. President, we stand losing

143
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,640
失去一个重要的摇摆州
control of an important swing state,

144
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,820
和议会多数党席位
our majority in the house,

145
00:08:57,820 --> 00:09:00,100
甚至是您的连任
and quite possibly your second term in office.

146
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:03,290
要扭转局势就得采取非常手段
Preventing all of that may require unconventional measures.

147
00:09:03,290 --> 00:09:04,720
别人会以为是我容不下他
It would look like I'm pushing him out.

148
00:09:04,970 --> 00:09:07,630
或者更糟  以为他是抛弃了我们
Or worse... that he's abandoning the administration.

149
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,050
